### 2.2 — EVENTS.FTH (système d'événements)

Avec `defer` maintenant disponible, un vrai système d'événements :

```forth
\ EVENTS.FTH

defer on-key-press     \ ( char -- )
defer on-key-release   \ ( char -- )
defer on-mouse-move    \ ( x y -- )
defer on-mouse-click   \ ( x y btn -- )
defer on-tick          \ ( ms -- )
defer on-resize        \ ( w h -- )
defer on-quit          \ ( -- )

: default-nop  drop ;
: default-nop2 drop drop ;
: default-nop3 drop drop drop ;

' default-nop  is on-key-press
' default-nop  is on-key-release
' default-nop2 is on-mouse-move
' default-nop3 is on-mouse-click
' default-nop  is on-tick
' default-nop2 is on-resize
' default-nop  is on-quit

: event-loop ( -- )
  begin
    \ Clavier
    touche? dup 0<> if on-key-press else drop then
    \ Souris
    souris? if
      souris on-mouse-move
    then
    \ Tick
    ticks on-tick
    \ Dessin
    16 ms
    \ Quitter ?
    exit-requested? if on-quit 1 else 0 then
  until ;
```

